@HumanLikeReasoner text
Use HumanLikeReasoner for bounded human-scale reasoning tasks that should be solved through an explicit generated reasoning program plus inspectable local solvers.
Prefer it for finite assignment, graph reachability, bounded numeric reasoning, small search problems, and mixed tasks where one statement combines several of those reasoning families.
The body may be a direct natural-language problem, a structured rewrite brief produced by logic-eval, or a JSON envelope that pins result_mode, program, or generation settings.
Prefer direct HumanLikeReasoner routing when the task is already clearly a bounded reasoning problem. Prefer AdvancedReasoner instead when the task becomes incomplete, probabilistic, causal, evidential, legal, scientific, normative, interpretive, or otherwise too open-world for a finite local solver profile.
